task:
ATOM 9 (documentation) — Document the now-shipped Play system as a coherent subsystem in ARCHITECTURE.md. The Play system was just built across atoms 1-8 of this priority and is fully landed and proven, but ARCHITECTURE.md only mentions 'plays' in the directory-layout section; there is no architecture-level description of the subsystem. Add one.

ADD a concise new section to ARCHITECTURE.md titled '## Play system' (place it logically near the other orchestration subsystem sections, e.g. after '## Persona Boundaries (CoCoder)' or '## Oz vs Debugger'). It must describe, accurately to the shipped code, what a Play is NOW (a typed contract with metadata, not just markdown injected into a prompt):
- the FIVE Play classes from the taxonomy (prompt-only; hybrid with deterministic precheck/gate; lifecycle-triggered; persona-requested; tool/API-triggered) — CITE ADR-0010 as the owner of the taxonomy, do not restate the whole decision;
- the contract schema fields (executionModel, triggerClass, purpose, allowedCallers, inputSchema, outputValidator, deterministicStep, commitMode, requiredCheckpoints, writeScope) — CITE packages/core/src/plays/types.ts as the owner;
- prompt-only vs HYBRID execution: the optional deterministicStep runs a real repo-root-relative script (ref->command convention: .mjs via node, else executable; refs may not escape the repo root) whose captured result either GATES the LLM (non-zero exit -> no LLM invocation) or FEEDS it (output injected into the prompt) — CITE packages/core/src/plays/dispatch.ts;
- the per-persona CAPABILITY MANIFEST injected into launch prompts (compact id/purpose/caller/trigger/input/write/mandatory-or-optional rows; full Play bodies are lazy-loaded only at dispatch, never injected wholesale);
- the TYPED Play request lane (personas request optional Plays via a structured handoff validated by the runner/daemon for persona, Play id, trigger class, input schema, assignment, and write scope) and the MANDATORY trigger registry (runner/daemon owns lifecycle/policy triggers such as wrap-up; personas do not decide them);
- output validation DRIVEN BY the declared outputValidator ref (one owner: the runner selects the validator from the Play's declared ref via the exported validatePlayOutput; e.g. wrap-up declares validators/founder-closeout) — CITE packages/core/src/runner/runner.ts and the existing docs/orchestration-contract-ownership.md entry, do not duplicate the closeout label contract;
- the one-level dispatch boundary (no recursive Play delegation, no multi-binding) — CITE ADR-0010 / the dispatch-boundary archive;
- the real-path PROOF that this works end to end: scripts/proof-hybrid-play.mjs exercises the real dispatch path with a real deterministic script, a real LLM invocation for the hybrid Play, and the runner-owned wrap-up trigger validated through the declared outputValidator ref.

STYLE / STANDARDS (enforced at verify):
- DERIVE FROM OWNERS, do not duplicate contracts. Match the existing docs/orchestration-contract-ownership.md and docs/onboarding-rebuild-ownermap.md citation style: point at the authoritative file/ADR for each concept rather than copying field lists, label orders, or allowed values. One owner per concept (Elegance standard).
- Correctness first, clarity second, elegance third: a fresh persona should read the section ONCE and understand the subsystem and where to look for each contract. Keep it tight — no atom-by-atom history, no run narrative.
- Add a matching entry under ARCHITECTURE.md's '## References' section pointing to ADR-0010, the Play types, dispatch, and the proof harness.
- Every file/path/ADR you cite MUST exist and be correct (verify each reference resolves to a real file and, where you give a section, that the section exists). Do not invent line numbers that will rot — prefer file/section references over line ranges unless the surrounding docs use line ranges.

MUST NOT: change any code, change ADR-0010 or any Play file, duplicate a contract that already has an owner, or touch unrelated ARCHITECTURE.md sections beyond the new section + the References entry.

WRITE-SCOPE: ARCHITECTURE.md (primary). You may add to docs/** only if a dedicated page is clearly better than an ARCHITECTURE.md section AND you cross-link it; default to the ARCHITECTURE.md section.

EXIT CRITERION (judgment-based — one-shot gated atom, not loop-amenable): report the full diff and, for EVERY file/ADR/path you cite, the evidence that it exists and is accurate (e.g. grep/ls showing the cited file and the cited symbol or section). State plainly that no contract was duplicated (each concept points at its owner) and that no code or Play files were changed. Do NOT run git.
